fields.description: You will need at least one Membership Type to use the Memberships module. Set pricing, expiration and renewal options here. For example, this is a 1-year membership that expires one year from the date of join or renewal. The member can renew their membership 95 days before expiration and up to 30 days after. They also have a 7-day grace period after expiration with member benefits.  https://tendenci.readthedocs.org/en/latest/topic-guides/memberships.html
fields.name: Basic Membership

fields.description: Many organizations offer a Student Membership at a discounted price. In this example, the membership is for one-year with 30 days either side of expiration to renew and no grace period. The renewal also requires approval so that enrollment can be verified prior to renewal.
fields.name: Student membership

fields.description: This controls the membership term for both the Corporation and the Individuals that join as part of the Corporate Membership. The renewal period defaults to 95 days prior to expiration and can be adjusted for fiscal year reporting requirements.
fields.name: Corporate Membership (Individual)
